## Context
DevOps + security reviews found two issues in pre-commit guard 5:

1. If uv is not installed, ticket validation is silently skipped.
   Should warn explicitly so the committer knows.

2. Guard validates ALL tickets in tickets/, not just staged ones.
   An already-broken unstaged ticket blocks unrelated commits.
   Should pass only staged .ticket file paths to the validator.

## Actions
1. Add explicit warning when uv is not found (not a hard fail —
   developer laptops may not have uv)
2. Pass staged .ticket file paths to validate_tickets.py instead
   of the whole directory
3. For cross-file checks (duplicate IDs), validate_tickets.py needs
   a mode where it loads all tickets as reference but only reports
   errors on the specified files — or just validate the full dir
   (current behavior) but accept the tradeoff

## Exit criteria
- Missing uv produces a visible warning
- Pre-commit validates staged files (or full dir with documented tradeoff)
